trans-unit.source: Exception occurs when the specified number of classes is less than the actual number of classes in a dataset used for counting.
trans-unit.target: Exception occurs when the specified number of classes is less than the actual number of classes in a dataset used for counting.

trans-unit.source: This error occurs when you are creating a count table and the label column contains a different number of classes than you specified in the module parameters.
trans-unit.target: This error occurs when you are creating a count table and the label column contains a different number of classes than you specified in the module parameters.

trans-unit.source: Check your dataset and find out exactly how many distinct values (possible classes) there are in the label column.
trans-unit.target: Check your dataset and find out exactly how many distinct values (possible classes) there are in the label column.

trans-unit.source: When you create the count table, you must specify at least this number of classes.
trans-unit.target: When you create the count table, you must specify at least this number of classes.

trans-unit.source: The count table cannot automatically determine the number of classes available -- -when you create the count table you cannot specify 0 or any number that is less than the actual number of classes in the label column.
